@startuml tmu_bars_to_dkey_security_grade_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title TMU Bars To DKEY Security Grade Signal Flow\n(TMU service mode + signal bars + drive state -> DKEY security grade and presence)

participant "TMU service bus" as TMU #F4F7FB
participant "Vehicle state bus" as Veh #E8F0FE
participant "DKEY\ndigital key owner" as DKEY #E8F7E8
participant "Digital key state bus" as DKeyBus #FFF4CC
participant "SMK / Door / PAK\naccess consumers" as Consumers #FFF4CC

== DKEY Inputs ==

TMU -> DKEY : frmTmuServiceStateMsg\nTmuServiceMode / SignalBars
Veh -> DKEY : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\ngDriveState
activate DKEY
DKEY -> DKEY : normalize stale TMU / vehicle inputs
DKEY -> DKEY : if dkeyState == 2 and signalBars >= 3\nthen SecurityGrade = 2
DKEY -> DKEY : else if tmuServiceMode > 0 and signalBars >= 1\nthen SecurityGrade = 1
DKEY -> DKEY : KeyPresence = (tmuServiceMode > 0 and signalBars > 0)
DKEY -> DKEY : derive DKeyState / AuthMode /\nVehicleAccessState / KeySyncAge
note right of DKEY
Representative inputs
- TmuServiceMode
- SignalBars
- gDriveState

Representative derived outputs
- SecurityGrade
- KeyPresence
- DKeyState
- AuthMode
- VehicleAccessState
end note

== DKEY Publish ==

DKEY -> DKeyBus : frmDigitalKeyStateMsg\nSecurityGrade / KeyPresence /\nDKeyState / AuthMode / VehicleAccessState
DKeyBus -> Consumers : digital key access and immobilizer consumers
deactivate DKEY

note over TMU, Consumers
Representative runtime chain
1. TMU service mode and signal bars reach DKEY with drive state
2. DKEY converts signal strength and service posture into security grade and presence
3. DKEY publishes the consolidated digital-key state
4. SMK, doors, and proximity access consumers use the resulting access posture
end note

@enduml
